{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":269,"text":"People love their automobiles."},{"time":1912,"text":"They allow us to go\nwhere we want to when we want to."},{"time":5000,"text":"They're a form of entertainment,"},{"time":6639,"text":"they're a form of art,"},{"time":8664,"text":"a pride of ownership."},{"time":10370,"text":"Songs are written about cars."},{"time":12063,"text":"Prince wrote a great song:\n\"Little Red Corvette.\""},{"time":14422,"text":"He didn't write \"Little Red Laptop\nComputer\" or \"Little Red Dirt Devil.\""},{"time":17896,"text":"He wrote about a car."},{"time":19114,"text":"One of my favorites has always been:"},{"time":21000,"text":"\"Make Love to Your Man in a Chevy Van,\""},{"time":22999,"text":"because that was my vehicle\nwhen I was in college."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26379,"text":"The fact is, when we do\nour market research around the world,"},{"time":29812,"text":"we see there's a nearly universal\naspiration on the part of people"},{"time":33829,"text":"to own an automobile --"},{"time":35007,"text":"750 million people\nin the world today own a car."},{"time":39797,"text":"And you say, boy, that's a lot."},{"time":41366,"text":"But you know what?"},{"time":42546,"text":"That's just 12 percent of the population."},{"time":44705,"text":"We really have to ask the question:"},{"time":46863,"text":"Can the world sustain\nthat number of automobiles?"},{"time":49606,"text":"And if you look at projections\nover the next 10 to 15 to 20 years,"},{"time":53498,"text":"it looks like the world\ncar park could grow"},{"time":56818,"text":"to on the order of 1.1 billion vehicles."},{"time":59777,"text":"If you park those end to end\nand wrap them around the Earth,"},{"time":63476,"text":"that would stretch\naround the Earth 125 times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66846,"text":"Now, we've made great progress\nwith automobile technology"},{"time":70156,"text":"over the last 100 years."},{"time":71821,"text":"Cars are dramatically cleaner,\ndramatically safer, more efficient"},{"time":75682,"text":"and radically more affordable\nthan they were 100 years ago."},{"time":79406,"text":"But the fact remains:"},{"time":80999,"text":"the fundamental DNA of the automobile\nhas stayed pretty much the same."},{"time":85499,"text":"If we were to reinvent the automobile\ntoday, rather than 100 years ago,"},{"time":89791,"text":"knowing what we know about the issues\nassociated with our product"},{"time":93620,"text":"and about the technologies\nthat exist today,"},{"time":96103,"text":"what would we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97322,"text":"We wanted something\nthat was really affordable."},{"time":99586,"text":"The fuel cell looked great:"},{"time":101293,"text":"one-tenth as many moving parts,"},{"time":103038,"text":"a fuel-cell propulsion system\nas an internal combustion engine,"},{"time":106187,"text":"and it emits just water."},{"time":107416,"text":"And we wanted to take\nadvantage of Moore's Law"},{"time":109802,"text":"with electronic controls and software,"},{"time":111667,"text":"and we absolutely wanted\nour car to be connected."},{"time":114730,"text":"So we embarked upon the reinvention\naround an electrochemical engine,"},{"time":118634,"text":"the fuel cell,"},{"time":119814,"text":"and hydrogen as the energy carrier."},{"time":121822,"text":"First was Autonomy."},{"time":123355,"text":"Autonomy really set the vision\nfor where we wanted to head."},{"time":126436,"text":"We embodied all of the key components\nof a fuel-cell propulsion system."},{"time":130500,"text":"We then had Autonomy\ndrivable with Hy-Wire,"},{"time":133195,"text":"and we showed Hy-Wire here\nat this conference last year."},{"time":136500,"text":"Hy-Wire is the world's first\ndrivable fuel cell,"},{"time":139687,"text":"and we have followed\nup that now with Sequel."},{"time":142500,"text":"And Sequel truly is a real car."},{"time":144500,"text":"So if we could run the video --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146859,"text":"(Futuristic music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154780,"text":"[Reinventing the Automobile]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193794,"text":"(Video) It truly is my great pleasure\nto introduce Sequel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213795,"text":"[Acceleration]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":218176,"text":"[Cruising]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":222133,"text":"[Steering]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226197,"text":"[Braking]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232817,"text":"But the real key question\nI'm sure that's on your mind:"},{"time":235594,"text":"Where is the hydrogen going to come from?"},{"time":237594,"text":"And secondly, when are these kinds\nof cars going to be available?"},{"time":240784,"text":"So let me talk about hydrogen first."},{"time":243008,"text":"The beauty of hydrogen is it can come\nfrom so many different sources:"},{"time":246650,"text":"it can come from fossil fuels,"},{"time":248437,"text":"it can come from any way\nthat you can create electricity,"},{"time":251222,"text":"including renewables."},{"time":252882,"text":"And it can come from biofuels."},{"time":254697,"text":"And that's quite exciting."},{"time":256239,"text":"The vision here is to have each local\ncommunity play to its natural strength"},{"time":260515,"text":"in creating the hydrogen."},{"time":261838,"text":"A lot of hydrogen is produced\ntoday in the world."},{"time":264214,"text":"It's produced to get\nsulfur out of gasoline --"},{"time":266522,"text":"which I find is somewhat ironic."},{"time":268353,"text":"It's produced in the fertilizer industry;"},{"time":270984,"text":"it's produced in the chemical\nmanufacturing industry."},{"time":274230,"text":"That hydrogen is being made"},{"time":275643,"text":"because there's a good\nbusiness reason for its use."},{"time":278332,"text":"But it tells us that we know\nhow to create it,"},{"time":280920,"text":"we know how to create it cost-effectively,"},{"time":283217,"text":"we know how to handle it safely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285508,"text":"We did an analysis"},{"time":286729,"text":"where you would have\na station in each city"},{"time":289349,"text":"with each of the 100 largest cities\nin the United States,"},{"time":292500,"text":"and located the stations"},{"time":294500,"text":"so you'd be no more than two miles\nfrom a station at any time."},{"time":297500,"text":"We put one every 25 miles on the freeway,"},{"time":299833,"text":"and it turns out that translates\ninto about 12,000 stations."},{"time":303862,"text":"And at a million dollars each,\nthat would be about 12 billion dollars."},{"time":307251,"text":"That's a lot of money."},{"time":308500,"text":"But if you built the Alaskan\npipeline today,"},{"time":310619,"text":"that's half of what the Alaskan\npipeline would cost."},{"time":313724,"text":"But the real exciting vision\nthat we see, truly, is home refueling,"},{"time":317748,"text":"much like recharging your laptop\nor recharging your cell phone."},{"time":321397,"text":"So we're pretty excited\nabout the future of hydrogen."},{"time":324460,"text":"We think it's a question of not whether,\nbut a question of when."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328500,"text":"What we've targeted for ourselves --"},{"time":330300,"text":"and we're making great progress\ntoward this goal --"},{"time":332849,"text":"is to have a propulsion system\nbased on hydrogen and fuel cells,"},{"time":336365,"text":"designed and validated,"},{"time":338111,"text":"that can go head-to-head\nwith the internal combustion engine."},{"time":341080,"text":"We're talking about obsoleting\nthe internal combustion engine,"},{"time":344111,"text":"and doing it in terms\nof affordability at scale volumes,"},{"time":347176,"text":"its performance and its durability."},{"time":349599,"text":"So that's what we're driving to for 2010."},{"time":352314,"text":"We haven't seen anything yet\nin our development work"},{"time":354816,"text":"that says that isn't possible."},{"time":356316,"text":"We actually think the future\nis going to be event-driven."},{"time":359460,"text":"So since we can't predict the future,"},{"time":361461,"text":"we want to spend a lot of our time\ntrying to create that future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364500,"text":"I'm very, very intrigued"},{"time":365944,"text":"by the fact that our cars and trucks\nsit idle 90 percent of the time:"},{"time":370499,"text":"they're parked all around us."},{"time":372722,"text":"They're usually parked within 100 feet\nof the people that own them."},{"time":376097,"text":"Now, if you take the power-generating\ncapability of an automobile"},{"time":379900,"text":"and you compare that to the electric grid\nin the United States,"},{"time":383153,"text":"it turns out that the power\nin four percent of the automobiles"},{"time":387770,"text":"equals that of the electric\ngrid of the US."},{"time":390357,"text":"That's a huge power-generating capability,"},{"time":393282,"text":"a mobile power-generating capability."},{"time":395412,"text":"And hydrogen and fuel cells\ngive us that opportunity"},{"time":398413,"text":"to actually use our cars and trucks\nwhen they're parked"},{"time":401215,"text":"to generate electricity for the grid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403216,"text":"We talked about swarm networks earlier."},{"time":405365,"text":"Talk about the ultimate swarm --\nhaving all of the processors"},{"time":408766,"text":"and all of the cars\nwhen they're sitting idle"},{"time":410934,"text":"being part of a global grid\nfor computing capability."},{"time":414460,"text":"We find that premise quite exciting."},{"time":417145,"text":"The automobile becomes,\nthen, an appliance --"},{"time":419407,"text":"not in a commodity sense,"},{"time":420707,"text":"but an appliance, mobile power,\nmobile platform"},{"time":423500,"text":"for information and computing\nand communication,"},{"time":426139,"text":"as well as a form of transportation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428500,"text":"And the key to all of this\nis to make it affordable,"},{"time":431151,"text":"to make it exciting,"},{"time":432326,"text":"to get it on a pathway where\nthere's a way to make money doing it."},{"time":435491,"text":"And again, this is a pretty\nbig march to take here."},{"time":438500,"text":"A lot of people say:"},{"time":439677,"text":"How do you sleep at night"},{"time":440895,"text":"when you're wrestling with a problem\nof that magnitude?"},{"time":443538,"text":"I tell them I sleep like a baby:\nI wake up crying every two hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446726,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":447893,"text":"Actually, the theme\nof this conference, I think,"},{"time":450215,"text":"has hit on one of the major keys\nto pull that off,"},{"time":452613,"text":"and that's relationships\nand working together."},{"time":454827,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456021,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459356,"text":"Chris Anderson: Larry, Larry -- wait,\nwait, wait. Larry, wait one sec."},{"time":464962,"text":"I've got so many questions\nI could ask you."},{"time":467368,"text":"I just want to ask one."},{"time":469329,"text":"You know, I could be wrong about this,"},{"time":471207,"text":"but my sense is that\nin the public mind today,"},{"time":474855,"text":"GM is not viewed as as serious\nabout some of these environmental ideas"},{"time":481280,"text":"as some of your Japanese\ncompetitors, maybe even as Ford."},{"time":485798,"text":"Are you serious about it,"},{"time":487219,"text":"and not just, you know,\nwhen the consumers want it,"},{"time":491500,"text":"when the regulators force us\nto do it, we will go there?"},{"time":494164,"text":"Will you guys really try\nand show leadership on this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":496690,"text":"Larry Burns: Absolutely.\nWe're absolutely serious."},{"time":499102,"text":"We're into this\nover a billion dollars already,"},{"time":501383,"text":"so I would hope people\nwould think we're serious"},{"time":503694,"text":"when we're spending that kind of money."},{"time":505703,"text":"And secondly, it's a fundamental\nbusiness proposition."},{"time":508735,"text":"I'll be honest with you;"},{"time":509915,"text":"we're into it for business\ngrowth opportunities."},{"time":512240,"text":"We can't grow our business\nunless we solve these problems."},{"time":515004,"text":"The growth of the auto industry\nwill be capped by sustainability issues"},{"time":518408,"text":"if we don't solve the problems."},{"time":519930,"text":"And there's a simple principle\nof strategy that says:"},{"time":522450,"text":"Do unto yourself\nbefore others do unto you."},{"time":524523,"text":"If we can see this possible\nfuture, others can, too."},{"time":527452,"text":"And we want to be the first one\nto create it, Chris."}]}]}